reviews.text:
Paris has its Eiffel Tower;
Egypt has its pyramids;
Beijing has its Forbidden City;

And Clermont-Ferrand has Trib's.
The human race is at its lowest in this place, thanks to its two restrooms, its two champagne FIFA rooms (the Lounge and the Mini Totem), its green and rustic decor, its tidy kitchen, its uncomfortable sofas that will delight any mutant, and of course, its oh-so-friendly staff. The smell isn't a problem for them, and the service is impeccable, allowing you to always find opponents for the legendary game that made this place famous. In short, don't run away while they last! We all remember the closure of the Totem... We hope for a happier outcome for this iconic Clermont nightlife spot.

Special mention for the balcony, which allows for deep discussions over a Koenigsbier. A place of addiction, a kind of Fifa Champagne shooting gallery, fortunately the walking repellent Peio allows us to get back on the right path and put us back on the right path thanks to his plague-ridden smell!
